[SN]TITLE[SN]
Carwyn Scott-Howell: Inquest opened into Alps ski death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A child who died in a skiing accident in France fell from a height sufficient to account for his death, an inquest in Newport has heard.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Carwyn Scott-Howell, seven, from Talybont-on-Usk, Powys, died while on a family holiday in the French Alps earlier this month.
The inquest heard his body was found on a ledge in the resort of Flaine after being separated from his family.
Gwent deputy coroner Wendy James adjourned the inquest until 22 June.
